How to add github project to eclipse
**********
Step1: Create a github account and login.
Step2: Start a project-->Create repository
Step3: Start Eclipse
Step4: Goto Perspective-->Search for "Git Repositories" in eclipse.
Step5: Create a project in eclipse or its fine if there is already a project.
Step6: Righclick on project-->Team-->Share-->Add to git reposiotory.
Step7: Commit and Push the project to the repository.
Step8: Commit and push every change in the repository.